<DIV2 N="36" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[XXXVI. &THORN;e Lamentacioun &thorn;at was bytwene vre lady and seynt Bernard.]</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot">So the title in Index. Title in D, 'Lamentacio sancti Bernardi de compassione beate Marie vir|ginis ex dulcissimi filii sui passione et eiusdem crudeli morte'; in T, 'La|mentacio sancte marie &amp; beati Bernardi.'</NOTE>Her is a gret lamentacion betwene vr ladi &amp; seint Bernard, Of cristes passion, hire dere sone, &thorn;at was so pyneful &amp; so hard.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>Ed. before, at my suggestion, in <I>Engl. Stud.</I>, 1885, vol. viii. p. 85 ff., by G. Kribel, from MS. Vernon and Cambridge Dd. 1, 1. I here give the text of MS. Vernon with various readings from MS. Dd. 1, 1, and two more MSS., Trin. Coll. Oxf. 57 f. (incomplete), and MS. L. 70. The poem is based on a Latin sermon attributed to St. Bernhard (ed. opp. Antw. 1616, col. 156, and in Migne Patr. Curs. Ser. II. vol. 182, col. 1133, Paris 1879; both edd. differ in some respects, the Engl. text rests more on that of the former ed.), with frequent addings from the Gospels (cf. v. 21-4). The poem is not to be ascribed to Richard Rolle, but to Richard Maidenstoon, the author of the Seven Penitential Psalms. Cf. Kribel, l. c. It is in 8-line stanzas of alternate rymes.</P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000306.tif" N="298">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L><MILESTONE N="cclxxxvi" UNIT="folio"> Lewed men be not lered in lore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Lewid L Lewede. D arn T bu&thorn; L &thorn;at beo&thorn;. T no&yogh;t. D lerid L lente, om. in T.</NOTE></L>
<L>As Clerkes ben in holi writ;<NOTE PLACE="foot">D clerkis. T be&thorn; L beo&thorn;. D writte.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;au&yogh; men prechen hem bi-fore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &thorn;e&yogh; L &thorn;ei, D &amp; &thorn;ouh. D preche L reden. TL before D euere-more.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Hit wol not wonen in heore wit:<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL It. DL wile T may. T no&yogh;t. D wone T dwellen. D hire T hare L here. D witte.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;erfore is &thorn;at I syke sore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D ffor &thorn;is it is. T y. DTL sike.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffor bro&thorn;urhede, as God hit bit,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D bretherhed TL bro&thorn;erhede. T it D vs, om. in L. D bitte.</NOTE></L>
<L>And, &yogh;if cristes wille wore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL if. D Cristis T godis L godes. D wil it. T were.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">Wel fayn I wolde amenden hit.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL om. Wel. TL Y wolde fayn. D amendin. D itte.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;if Crist haue send mon wit at wille,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T And &yogh;if. TL god. D sent TL lent. DTL vs. D witt &amp;.</NOTE></L>
<L>Craft of Clergye, for to preche,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL &amp; craft.</NOTE></L>
<L>Alle hise hestes scholde we fulfille<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL We schuld (L sholde T shullen) fayn his hestis (T his hestis fayn). T fulfelle.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">As ferfor&thorn; as we mihten areche.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D ferfort TL fer. D has. DTL oure wit. L myghte T may D wold. TL reche.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;onge and olde, holde&thorn; ow stille:<NOTE PLACE="foot">D hold &yogh;ow TL loude &amp;.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffor bro&thorn;erhed I wol ow teche&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">D As bretherin alle. DL wile T wil. DT &yogh;ow L &yogh;ou.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e Mon &thorn;at con, and teche nille,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D ffor he T ffor who so L Who so. DTL om. &thorn;at. DTL can. D &amp; ha&thorn; no wille.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">He mai haue drede of godes wreche.<NOTE PLACE="foot">L Him. DTL om. haue; T doute L douten D sore dowte. D Cristis T harde.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;erfore ichaue on Englisch wrou&yogh;t,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL I haue. TL in. L englissh. D wrouht L wroughte.</NOTE></L>
<L>Seint<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> As</NOTE> Bernard witnesse&thorn; in Latyn&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL As B. seyth (TL sei&thorn;) in his l.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mon may be glad in al his &thorn;ou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL A man D He. L beo. T wel glad L blithe. TL om. al; T om. his. L thoughte.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20">&THORN;at his wit ha&thorn; leid &thorn;er-In.<NOTE PLACE="foot">L al his. D besynes L tente. T ha&thorn; leyd his wit. D om. ha&thorn;; leyde.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e gospel nul I forsake nou&yogh;t,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D wile forsake it L wel forsake I T forsake&thorn; it.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;au&yogh; hit be writen in parchemyn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL &thorn;at is wryten D ffor he it wrot.</NOTE></L>
<L>Seynt Iones word,<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> bok</NOTE> and hit be sou&yogh;t,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Iohanes D Iohn his L Ion in his. DTL bok if it. L beo soughte.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">&THORN;er-of hit wole be witnes myn.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL Herof. T Wil be &thorn;erof. TL om. hit. D ben. DT witnesse.</NOTE></L>
<L>While Ihesu crist on eor&thorn;e eode,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D &thorn;at while &thorn;at L &thorn;e while &thorn;at. DTL god inst. of Ihesu crist. DT erthe. T &yogh;ede L &yogh;eode D &yogh;ode.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000307.tif" N="299"></L>
<L>Mony of his Miracles writen &thorn;ei were:<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL Alle his. D myraclis T workes L werkes. D wretin. DTL om. &thorn;ei.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er nis no mon &thorn;at mihte rede<NOTE PLACE="foot">DT is. L om. no. T man DL clerk. D om. &thorn;at; D in boke. D may T cou&thorn;e L coude.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">&THORN;e goodnesse &thorn;at he dude here.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D goodnes T guodnesse L godenesse. DL dide. D to vs here. T &thorn;ere.</NOTE></L>
<L>Men and wymmen, &yogh;e schulen haue mede,<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL Man. D women TL woman. D schul T may L mowe. D han.</NOTE></L>
<L>Lustene&thorn; alle now me I-feere;<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL If (TL And) &yogh;e me (om. in TL) listne (T wille lestyn) alle in fere (T yfere).</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;if I sigge mis, take&thorn; good hede,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL mys-say. D taki&thorn;. T guod L goede.</NOTE></L>
<L N="32">And wisse&thorn; me, &thorn;at hit betere were.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D om. And. DT wisse. D to telle &thorn;e beste to lere. L as inst. of &thorn;at hit. T y inst. of hit. L better.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffader and sone and holy gost,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D om. and(1).</NOTE></L>
<L>Al-mihtiful god in Trinite,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Almy&yogh;tful DL Almyhti. DT trenyte L trinitee.</NOTE></L>
<L>Myn hope is on &thorn;i Modur most,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Mi mone TL My mynde. D to the. TL moder D modir.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">fful of grace and of pite:<NOTE PLACE="foot">L mercy. T pete.</NOTE></L>
