<L>Such grace &thorn;enne &thorn;ow sende me<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Swich g. lord, T Lord such g., L Lorde sende suche g.; DTL om. &thorn;enne. L om. &thorn;ow; T sende &thorn;ou. DL to me.</NOTE></L>
<L>Sum word to speken wi&thorn;-outen bost,<NOTE PLACE="foot">L Som. DL speke. DL wi&thorn;-out(e).</NOTE></L>
<L N="40">&THORN;at sum men mowe &thorn;e beter be.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D sum man T many folk L mankynde. DT may, om. in L. DT betere L bettere. L beo.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Gret del hit is to speke and say<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL It is gret dool (T del L deol) to telle.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of him &thorn;at dyed on &thorn;e Roode,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D god T ihesu. DT deyde L diede. DL vpon T oppon. DTL rode.</NOTE></L>
<L>How he vppon &thorn;e gode ffriday<NOTE PLACE="foot">T om. he. L on. D good T guode.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">ffor vs &thorn;enne schedde his herte-blode;<NOTE PLACE="foot">D vs alle. DTL om. &thorn;enne. D schad T shadde. D om. herte; L suete.</NOTE></L>
<L>Alle hise disciples flowen a-way,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL his. D disciplis T deciples. D fled T fledden L fledde.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffor doute of de&thorn; &thorn;ei were nei&yogh; wode:<NOTE PLACE="foot">D But Marie &amp; Iohn be him stode. TL drede. T ne&yogh; L ney.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er nis no tonge &thorn;at telle may<NOTE PLACE="foot">DT is. L om. no. D tunge. D tellin.</NOTE></L>
<L N="48">&THORN;e serwe of Marie, his moder gode.<NOTE PLACE="foot">T sorwe L sorwes D goodnesse. DL om. Marie. D good T guode.</NOTE></L>
<L><NOTE PLACE="marg">Here begins the Latin text.</NOTE>Heo him bar bo&thorn;e god and Mon,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL ffor sche. DTL as inst. of bo&thorn;e, DT man.</NOTE></L>
<L>And si&thorn;en him clepede swete Ihesu,<NOTE PLACE="foot">L sithe T sethe D setthe. DTL clepid (T clepude) him. DTL om. swete.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000308.tif" N="300"></L>
<L>And offrede him to Symeon&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Sche. D offerid. D Symean.</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">fful wel &thorn;e prophete him he kneu&yogh;!<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL om. fful. D &THORN;at prophete ful wel. DTL his lord knew.</NOTE></L>
<L>An Angel warnede vre ladi &thorn;on<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &thorn;e. D aungil. D warnid. TL w. hem of &thorn;er (L here) fon. D &thorn;an.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of kyng Heroude, &thorn;at was vntrew&yogh;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &amp; of. TL Eroude (L heroude) &thorn;e kynge v. (&thorn;at was om.).</NOTE></L>
<L>And bad hire in to Egipte gon<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL hem. D vnto T intil. D Egipt. D gan.</NOTE></L>
<L N="56">ffor doute of de&thorn; of mony a Iew&yogh;.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL drede. D dr. of &thorn;at feloun Iew. TL many. T gew L gewe.</NOTE></L>
<L>Euer was Marie glad I-now&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL wel inst. of glad. D anow.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whon heo hire swete sone se&yogh;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL Whan T Whanne. DT sche. DTL seye.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whoderward &thorn;at Ihesu drou&yogh;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Whyderward so D Whedir &thorn;at euere. D drow L drouhe.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">He nas neuere out of hire e&yogh;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL was. T here. DTL eye.</NOTE></L>
<L>Si&thorn;en men duden him gret wou&yogh;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Setthe T suthen. D &thorn;e Iewis. DL dide. D wow L wouh.</NOTE></L>
<L>Harde peynes heo sei&yogh; hym drei&yogh;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D peynys. DTL sche. T se&yogh; L say D saw. T dreye DL drye.</NOTE></L>
<L>His honden were<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> om.</NOTE> nayled to a bou&yogh;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D hand T handes L hondes. DTL om. were. D naylid. TL til D vpon. D bow L bouhe.</NOTE></L>
<L N="64">Vppon a treo honged wel hei&yogh;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL &amp; on. D &thorn;e cros L a cros. TL hongen D &thorn;ei heng. DT him L on; wel om. in DTL. DTL heye.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;au&yogh; heo weore wo no wonder nas:<NOTE PLACE="foot">L &thorn;auhe T &thorn;e&yogh; D &thorn;ow. DT sche. DTL were. L om. wo no. D wunder. DT was.</NOTE></L>
<L>Heo sei&yogh; hym blodi, bodi and croun,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Hy D Sche. T se&yogh; L seye D saw. T blede L bleden. D crowne L croune.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hire sone &thorn;at so gultles was,<NOTE PLACE="foot">L Hire oune s. DT &thorn;at was so, om. in L; L al. DL gilteles.</NOTE></L>
<L N="68">Wi&thorn; stremes of blod he ron a-doun.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Stremyd of blod &thorn;at ran riht downe T Of blod &thorn;e strem ran adoun L On strem &thorn;e blode ran adoune.</NOTE></L>
<L>To sen his peynes was gret pres,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D seen L seon T se. D peynys L peyne. D &thorn;er was. D om. gret.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wymmen folewede him &thorn;orw &thorn;e toun,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D women. DT him folewid (folwede) L foleweden him. T &thorn;orghe L &thorn;oruh. D towne.</NOTE></L>
<L>Sore wepynge, wi&thorn;-outen lees,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D weping T wepende. DL wi&thorn;-oute. DT les.</NOTE></L>
