<L>And spac wordes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> a word</NOTE> of gret pite<NOTE PLACE="foot">D seyde. DTL a word.</NOTE></L>
<L>To &thorn;e wymmen &thorn;at &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> he dide, <I>or</I> he</NOTE> speke,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T And to L Ande &thorn;us to. D women. D he dide TL he, inst. of &thorn;at &thorn;er.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000309.tif" N="301"></L>
<L N="76">And seide: "Wepe&thorn; not for me!<NOTE PLACE="foot">L weope&thorn; D wepit T ne wepe &yogh;e. T nou&yogh;t L nouhte.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffor &yogh;oure children &yogh;e mowe wepe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">TLD But (wepi&thorn; D) for &yogh;ow (T &yogh;ow-selue) &amp; &yogh;oure children (D childer) eke.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at do&thorn; me schome, as &yogh;e mowe se."<NOTE PLACE="foot">D &thorn;ei DTL don. TL shame D sorow. D may. L seo.</NOTE></L>
<L>No wonder &thorn;ou&yogh; hire herte breke,<NOTE PLACE="foot">TL om. No. T Wonder it was. D if TL &thorn;at. DTL Maries. D myhte br., TL ne br.</NOTE></L>
<L N="80">&THORN;at sei&yogh; hir sone so beten be!<NOTE PLACE="foot">D saw. D betin. L beo.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whon he was beten wi&thorn; scourges sore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL Whan T Whanne. D betin &amp; scorgid s., TL beten swi&thorn;e s.</NOTE></L>
<L>Alle his frendes were from hym gon;<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &amp; alle D om. Alle. D frendis L freondes. T were fro him g., L fro him conne g., D fled fro him good wone.</NOTE></L>
