<L N="95">To him wel feire speken<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. spenken</NOTE> heo gon,<NOTE PLACE="foot">TLD &amp; sche (L heo) ful (D him) faire fraynede him &thorn;an (D freyne gan).</NOTE></L>
<L>What was his wille to asken &thorn;o.<NOTE PLACE="marg">vv. 33-6 added by the poet.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">D To witen what his wil was &thorn;o. L aske T aske hire. L so.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"LAdi, &yogh;if hit be &thorn;i wille,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D He seyde Ladi L Lauedy he seide. T Leuedy. L were &yogh;oure.</NOTE></L>
<L>Tel me, as &thorn;ou art heuene-qwene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL Telle.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hou &thorn;at &thorn;ou weope &thorn;in herte fille,<NOTE PLACE="foot">L Hou D If T Whanne; DTL om. &thorn;at. T wep D wepte.</NOTE></L>
<L N="100">Whon &thorn;ei duden &thorn;i sone to scheme,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL Whan men. T dude DL dide. DTL &thorn;at tene.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000310.tif" N="302"></L>
<L>Whon &thorn;ei him bounden and beoten ille<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL om. whon &thorn;ei: Bounden (D Boundin) him &amp; beten (DT betin) him (om. in L) ille.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Corounden him wi&thorn; &thorn;ornes kene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D crownid T crounede L crouneden. D thornis.</NOTE></L>
<L>And<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> om.</NOTE> [he] bar &thorn;e Crois meke and stille<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL He. L his cros D him euere. D mylde L myldeliche T bo&thorn;e mylde.</NOTE></L>
<L N="104">As &thorn;au&yogh; on hym non harm were sene.<NOTE PLACE="foot">D As non harm on him had bene TL As him were no sorwe sene.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Ladi," seide Bernard, "weore &thorn;ou &thorn;ere &thorn;o,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL Swete ladi (T lefdy L lauedy). DTL om. seide Bernard. DTL were.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er Men him bounden and beoten so fast?<NOTE PLACE="foot">DT Whan L &thorn;o. T &thorn;e&yogh;. DTL betin (L bete) &amp; bounden. DTL om. so; L him. DL faste.</NOTE></L>
<L>I wot &thorn;ou weore not fer him fro,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D hope. DTL were. T no&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L N="108">&THORN;in herte was stif and ful studefast!<NOTE PLACE="foot">DL is. DTL so. TL om. stif and. DTL om. ful. D stedfaste T stedefast L stedefaste.</NOTE></L>
<L>Allas! whi nere myn herte so?<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Allas allas whi dide &thorn;ei so. TL my loue.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whi is myn now so vnwrast?<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL myn herte; now om. DL vnwraste.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whi nolde hit cleue or breke a-two,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D &THORN;at it ne wile cleue in two. TL breke (L berste) or cleue.</NOTE></L>
<L N="112">Or wepe while &thorn;at hit wolde last?<NOTE PLACE="marg">A stanza om.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>T &amp;. DTL whil my lyf may. DL laste.</P><P>DTL then have the following stanza: Ladi, I am in (om. in L) greet longing To seen (T se L seo) &thorn;at (T &thorn;e) sihte (T si&yogh;t) &thorn;at &thorn;ou there (om. in L) seye, Whan (L Hou) &thorn;ou gan (T be-gan L gonne) &thorn;in handis (T honden L hondes) (to T) wring (wringe), &THORN;e teris (TL teres) ran (L ronnen) doun be (L of) &thorn;in eye. &THORN;ou saw (T se&yogh; L seye) &thorn;i sone wi&thorn; naylis (TL nayles) sting (T stynge L stronge), &amp; (om. in L) on a tre (L treo) &thorn;ei (om. in TL) heng (TL hongen) him (L on) heye. Whi ne were (TL nere) myn herte in (L on) &thorn;i mournyng, Whan (L &thorn;o) &thorn;ou him saw (T se&yogh;e L seye) swich (T &thorn;e L &thorn;o) peyne (T pynes L peynes) drye (TL dreye)?</P></NOTE></L>
<L>"Tel me &thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>al.</I> Allas for</NOTE> serwe &thorn;in herte was in,<NOTE PLACE="foot">DTL Allas for (TL &thorn;e) sorwe. L &thorn;at &thorn;ou were. D &thorn;in h. myhte kyne. TL ynne.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whon &thorn;ou se&yogh;e &thorn;in oune fode,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D saw L seye. D owne T herte.</NOTE></L>
<L>Godes sone, his hed doun lyn,<NOTE PLACE="foot">D Goddis T Godis. D heuid. DL clyne T clynne.</NOTE></L>
